      {
        "id": 2830228,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-03-06T02:58:28.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"5\" data-topic=\"158919\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Just had it last week. I don\u2019t see an issue opening it now. Way better than 2002 regular. Rep told me they sometimes do different dosage things with the different releases.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>To me, the divergence between 2002 P1 (as we may call the original disgorgement for clarity) and 2002 P2 are not very pronounced when you have them side by side, which I have done a number of times. The differences, as far as we are told, are triage under cork and somewhat lower dosage for P2, and there is less than a decade separating P1 and P2 in the 2002 vintage.</p>",
        "post_number": 6,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 7,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-03T16:56:24.912Z",
        "reply_count": 0,
        "reply_to_post_number": null,
        "quote_count": 1,
